HEADWORD: Menagerie
<hw>Men*ag"er*ie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧nagerie</ets>, fr. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧nager</ets> to keep
house, <ets>m⟦eacute⟧nage</ets> household. See <er>Menial</er>,
<er>Mansion</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A place where animals are kept
and trained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A collection of wild or exotic animals, kept for
exhibition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

